<p>
As @birgire alluded to, this is because your action is hooked later than when the core action runs, you'll need to hook in at priority 0 or lower: <em>edit: I originally said 9, but that doesn't work, use <code>0</code> or <code>-1</code> and it will work.</em>
</p>
<pre class="wiki">add_action( 'wp_ajax_edit-theme-plugin-file', function() {
	// Returns a failure for all edit attempts
	die( '-1' );
}, 0 );
</pre><p>
I'm marking this as <code>worksforme</code> as the above code works as expected.
</p>
